HTML was created by Sir Tim Berners-Lee while working at CERN,  aimed to solve the problem of linking multiple documents to ease it's consumption.
Please feel free to read more about it,  on Wikipedia.

1. HTML Hypertext Markup Language creates documents composed of tags,  which can represent data and media,  like videos, audio and images.
HTML is usually assisted by CSS and ES6 in order to create dinamyc and beautiful documents.  Each html document is represented and visualized through a Browser,  a kind of application that interprets HTML code and renders the desired document in what is common referred to web page.

2. Tags.  Are the building blocks of any html document.  Tags are represented by <[tag name]></[tag name]>,  a pair of opening and closing tags.

3. Hello World.
```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>This is a title</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>Hello world!</p>
  </body>
</html>
```

3. Hyperlinks:  Enable any string to be clicked and open a new document which is referenced by the content of the href tag,  named URL : Universal Resource Locator
remember Sit Tom Barnes Lee

<a href"/img/logo1.png" >
  Destination
</a>

